fields.title: August 14-16: Manitowish Waters, WI
fields.content:
Danielle and Greg have traveled to many places since they met nearly 5 year ago. Born on a hilltop in St. Peter, MN, their love would carry them from the bustling metropolis of Seoul, South Korea to the low plains of Southern Hungary and eventually to Washington, DC. This summer they invite you to join them in the land of moose, mosquitos, and muskies for a celebration of the first five, and a toast to the many more as they join each other in marriage. Join them for a weekend of joyous celebration at Chippewa Resort on the sunny shores of Wisconsin's Lake Manitowish.

Photo: Danielle and Greg at Washington's Hay Adams Hotel.

fields.title: What the Heck is a Manitowish!?
fields.content:
Manitowish Waters is a town of about 650 souls located in Vilas County, Wisconsin. It boasts a chain of lakes 10 members strong, and is famous for the Skiing Skeeters and Little Bohemia Lodge where "public enemy number 1" John Dillinger engaged in a shoot out with the FBI. Driving up Highway 51 from Madison it is easy to recall Johnny Deep's portrayal of Dillinger as you pass the lodge. The area is also known for it's access to a variety of outdoor activities and a local artist community. And it's so close to Michigan, you might even catch a lost Yooper on his way back from da bait shop!

For some ideas about what you might do while you're in town for our wedding, see our itinerary page, and our where to stay page for other hotels in the area, and for more information about Manitowish Waters you can check out their website and download an official visitor's guide.

Photo: The registration building at Chippewa Retreat.

fields.description: directions from MKE, ORD, MSP, and MSN
fields.title: How to get here:
fields.content:
Chippewa Retreat is located about 4 hours North of Madison and 4 and a half hours Northeast of the Twin Cities. Those coming to the wedding from out of state should consider flying into the Twin Cities (MSP), Madison (MSN), Milwaukee (MKE) or Chicago (ORD).

For specific directions, see the appropriate section below:

  • From the Twin Cities (Minneapolis-St.Paul International)
  • From Madison (Dane County Regional)
  • From Chicago (O'Hare International)
  • From Milwaukee (Gen. Mitchell International)

Minneapolis-St. Paul International Airport (about 4:30):

  1. Follow I-494 to I-94 E toward Eau Claire, Madison, and Chicago
  2. From I-94 E take exit 52 for WI Highway 29 E
  3. Take WI 29 all the way to Wausau and follow signs for WI-51 N
  4. From WI-51, turn left on Deer Park Rd.

Madison-Dane County Regional Airport (about 4:00):

  1. From Dane County Regional Airport follow Packers Ave. North to County Road CV
  2. From County Road CV merge onto WI-51 N and then take the exit for I-39N/I-90/94 W
  3. Follow I-39 N until it becomes WI-51 N in Wausau
  4. From WI-51, turn left on Deer Park Rd.

From Chicago-O'Hare International Airport (about 5:30):

  1. Take I-94 W to Milwaukee
  2. Take Exit 317 for I-43 S and follow signs for I-894 W
  3. Continue onto US Highway 45 N
  4. Exit for US 41 N
  5. Exit for US 45 N in Oshkosh
  6. Follow signs for Hwy 10 W to Stevens Point
  7. Take I-39/WI-51 N to Wausau
  8. From WI-51 turn left on Deer Park Rd.

From Milwaukee—Gen. Mitchell Airport (about 4:30)

  1. From I-94W merge onto I-43 and follow signs for I-894 W
  2. Continue onto US Highway 45 N
  3. Exit for US 41 N
  4. Exit for US 45 N in Oshkosh
  5. Follow signs for Hwy 10 W to Stevens Point
  6. Take I-39/WI-51 N to Wausau
  7. From WI-51 turn left on Deer Park Rd.

fields.description: Hotels and accommodations near the wedding.
fields.title: Where to stay
fields.content:
We encourage our guests to stay at Chippewa Retreat and have negotiated a special rate for the weekend for anyone who would like to stay on site. Chippewa Retreat has lodging options ranging from large cabins housing up to 10 people to smaller two bedroom apartments suitable for a group of 4. All of these options includes at least one bathroom and a full kitchen in the unit. They, unfortunately, do not have standard hotel rooms and we understand if some people will want to stay elsewhere. For those who might want to take this option, we recommend the hotels listed below. If these are booked before you get a chance, there are also many hotels in nearby Minocqua, WI.

Voss' Birchwood Lodge

The Voss family has owned this hotel, restaurant and resort for more than 100 years and are on the fifth generation of ownership. Voss' has standard hotel rooms with an excellent view of Spider Lake (one of the Manitowish lakes) as well as small cabins available. The lodge is located directly across Highway 51 from Chippewa Retreat and would be a short walk from the wedding and reception site.

Pea Patch Saloon

Boasting the "best burger by a dam site," (Greg can confirm the burger is top notch) the Pea Patch Saloon is located on County Road W, about a 5 minute drive North on Hwy. 51 from Chippewa Retreat. They offer affordable accommodations on the shores of Vance Lake (also one of the Manitowish Lakes) and access to the Toy Lake Swamp State Natural Area.

Timberline Inn

About 4 miles North of Chippewa Retreat between Rest and Vance Lakes, Timberline has a range of rooms from standard, double-queen bedrooms to king bedrooms with built-in fireplaces. Rooms here range from $89 per night to $170.

fields.title: About the Couple
fields.content:
Photo: Greg and Danielle after Gustavus Graduation, 2009.
Photo: Greg and Danielle after Gustavus Graduation, 2009.

Danielle and Greg first started dating in March 2009 while they were wrapping up their senior year at Gustavus Adolphus College. Their relationship started over dinner at Danielle's house where the couple swapped stories of their recent travels, Greg to China and Danielle to an organic farm in Bonifay, FL. But word has it they fell in love when they discovered their common love of public radio podcasts. Danielle was more interested in This American Life than this newfangled show called RadioLab Greg was so avidly proselytizing, but she gave it a shot and promptly added it to her collection of over 100,000 episodes.

After graduating in June, they embarked upon the travel experience of a lifetime, a year teaching English in South Korea. Their passion for professional travel eventually brought them to the homely city of Kaposvár, Hungary where they taught in public elementary and high schools. Over the course of those two years they learned that true love means helping each other through difficult times and challenging each other to learn new things about each other and the world. And the challenges yielded one rewarding experience after the next.

They decided it was time to come home to start graduate school in Washington, DC and start their lives stateside. After two years in DC they heard the Land of the Morning Calm calling them and headed back to Ilsan, South Korea, their one-time home, and during a walk around Lake Park, Greg asked Danielle to marry him.
